## Agent final message

> Written to `query99.preql` and validated successfully. The query:
> 
> - Imports `raw.catalog_sales` (the catalog sales fact)
> - Filters to ship year = 2000, and only rows where warehouse, ship_mode, and call_center are all not null
> - Buckets shipping lag (days_to_ship) into five columns using filtered aggregates: ≤30, 31–60, 61–90, 91–120, >120
> - Uses `coalesce(..., 0)` so empty buckets show 0 not null
> - Groups by first 20 chars of warehouse name, ship mode type, and lowercased call center name
> - Orders with nulls first per spec
> - Limits to 100 rows
> 
> Result: 90 rows returned — all lag_91_to_120 and lag_121_or_more values are 0 (no catalog sales in year 2000 with shipping beyond 90 days for these records).

